AIM: 
To write a C program to swap two numbers using call by value. 
 
 
ALGORITHM: 
1. Start the program. 
2. Declare two integer variables a and b. 
3. Read two integer values from the user. 
4. Call a function swapValue(a, b) that swaps the values locally. 
5. Print the numbers after function call. 
6. Stop the program. 
 
 
PROGRAM: 
#include <stdio.h> 
void swapValue(int x, int y) { 
int temp; 
temp = x; 
x = y; 
y = temp; 
printf("Inside function (Call by Value): a = %d, b = %d\n", x, y); 
} 
int main() { 
int a, b; 
printf("Enter two numbers: "); 
scanf("%d %d", &a, &b); 
swapValue(a, b); 
printf("After function call (Main): a = %d, b = %d\n", a, b); 
return 0; 
} 
 
SAMPLE OUTPUT: 
Enter two numbers: 10 20 
Inside function (Call by Value): a = 20, b = 10 
After function call (Main): a = 10, b = 20
